bug.summary: Update installation instruction for system libs: libgomp1, etc.
bug.description:
Hey guys, I am new to this project so I apologies in advanced if I have run into a simple error. I did try searching before creating a ticket. I wanted to test out the pretrained models on some audio files. I fired up a fresh VPS and installed the python package. Here are the steps I took, and the error I got:
Fire up fresh Ubuntu 17.04 VPS Install PIP Install deepspeech Download deepspeech-0.1.0-models.tar.gz Extract the files in the tar - this gives me the following: https://i.imgur.com/vFhO6mk.png Run the command deepspeech output_graph.pb my_audio.wav alphabet.txt lm.binary trie I get the following error:
<denchmark-link:https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1628446/33249568-420709d8-d390-11e7-946b-aff71c52a2ed.png></denchmark-link>
Thanks
